The paper discusses instrumenting programs for run-time checking of properties, which is a common technique in dynamic languages such as Prolog. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a method that uses static analysis to estimate run-time checking overhead, which is related to software performance (cs.SE). The paper also extends an existing assertion verification framework, which is related to logic (cs.LO). Furthermore, the paper discusses the need to reduce run-time overhead, which is related to computer security (cs.CR) and system and control (cs.SY).
